transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling Viagra. My name is Jessie. Can I get your first and—

Speaker 2: Last name?

Speaker 1: Teddy Smith.

Speaker 2: Teddy Smith? T-E-D-D-Y?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Just a moment, Mr. Smith. Yeah, your name looks a little messed up here. It says P-D-A-N.

Speaker 1: Here we go. Teddy Daniel Smith. All right. Can I get your zip code?

Speaker 2: Ma'am?

Speaker 1: Can I get your zip code?

Speaker 2: Three-six-three-four-five.

Speaker 1: Are you at 109 Holman in Headlands, Alabama?

Speaker 2: Yes, ma'am.

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: All right. So you're calling about your prescription. Did you need to change the frequency or did—

Speaker 1: You want to try some different pills? What can I help you with?

Speaker 2: I just wanted to cancel it. Cancel the prescription.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay. I can do that. Are you looking to cancel it just because you don't want to get any—

Speaker 1: More for now?

Speaker 2: Yeah, yeah.

Speaker 1: I can switch it to on-demand so that way you're not, you know, stockpiled.

Speaker 2: Well, I just want to cancel it for now and I'll call back if I, you know, need more.

Speaker 1: Sure. Here's a suggestion for you to keep your prescription active because you do need—

Speaker 2: To have the prescription active to actually place orders down the line, right? I can switch—

Speaker 1: It to on-demand so that way you don't get charged anything. You don't get anything monthly—

Speaker 2: Or every two months. Just order whenever you feel like it. Okay? So you can call in.

Speaker 1: I just want to cancel it all for right now. That's all I want to do, just cancel it all.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: I understand. When we cancel it for right now, and I know you're trying to shoot me—

Speaker 2: Off the phone so you can cancel it, I need to tell you exactly what to do because what—

Speaker 1: Happens is people call back and they're upset when they can't place orders. Okay? So this—

Speaker 2: Is full disclosure. Once we cancel it, you can't re-up the prescription. As long as you're—

Speaker 1: Okay with that, then we're fine.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'm fine.

Speaker 1: Okay, great. So yeah, you can't place an order in the future, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right. Thanks a lot. Bye-bye.
